310 g Chicken Breast Tenders
170 g Orzo
½ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
113 mL Cream
4 tbsp BBQ Sauce
1 tbsp Cream Sauce Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Chicken Broth Concentrate
56 g Green Peas
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add orzo and peas to the boiling water. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 10-12 min.
Drain and reserve 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) of pasta water. Return orzo and peas to the same pot, off heat.

Meanwhile, pat chicken dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then chicken breast tenders. Sear until golden-brown and cooked through, 3-4 min per side.**
Remove pan from heat. Add BBQ sauce. Toss to coat.

Meanwhile, heat a small pot over medium-high heat.
When hot add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter. Swirl pot to melt.
Add Cream Sauce Spice Blend. Cook, whisking often, until combined, 1 min.
Add cream, broth concentrate and pasta water. Cook, whisking until combined, 1 min.
Add cheese and whisk until cheese melts and sauce thickens, 1-2 min.

Add cheese sauce to the pot with orzo. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Divide cheesy orzo between bowls.
Top with the BBQ-sauced chicken tenders.